Ç—Ä–∞–Ω—É –ø—Ä–æ–∏—Å—Ö–æ–∂–¥–µ–Ω–∏—è –æ—Å—Ç–∞—Ç—å—Å—è –≤ –ü–æ–ª—å—à–µ –ø–æ –±–µ–∑–≤–∏–∑–æ–≤–æ–º—É –ø—Ä–µ–±—ã–≤–∞–Ω–∏—é —Å –±–∏–æ–º–µ—Ç—Ä–∏—á–µ—Å–∫–∏–º –ø–∞—Å–ø–æ—Ä—Ç–æ–º –ø–æ—Å–ª–µ –∏—Å—Ç–µ—á–µ–Ω–∏—è —Å—Ä–æ–∫–∞ –¥–µ–π—Å—Ç–≤–∏—è –ø–æ–ª—å—Å–∫–æ–π –≤–∏–∑—ã —Ç–∏–ø–∞ D?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>–î–∞. –ï—Å–ª–∏ –ø–æ–ª—å—Å–∫–∏–º –≤—ä–µ–∑–¥–Ω—ã–º –¥–æ–∫—É–º–µ–Ω—Ç–æ–º –±—ã–ª–∞ –ø–æ–ª—å—Å–∫–∞—è –Ω–∞—Ü–∏–æ–Ω–∞–ª—å–Ω–∞—è –≤–∏–∑–∞ —Ç–∏–ø–∞ D, –∏ –µ—Å–ª–∏ —É –≤–∞—Å –µ—Å—Ç—å –±–∏–æ–º–µ—Ç—Ä–∏—á–µ—Å–∫–∏–π –ø–∞—Å–ø–æ—Ä—Ç, –≤—ã –º–æ–∂–µ—Ç–µ –ø—Ä–æ–¥–ª–∏—Ç—å —Å–≤–æ–µ –ø—Ä–µ–±—ã–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ –≤ –ü–æ–ª—å—à–µ –≤ —Å–æ–æ—Ç–≤–µ—Ç—Å—Ç–≤–∏–∏ —Å –±–µ–∑–≤–∏–∑–æ–≤—ã–º —Ä–µ–∂–∏–º–æ–º, –ø—Ä–∏ —É—Å–ª–æ–≤–∏–∏, —á—Ç–æ –≤—ã –µ—â–µ –Ω–µ –∏—Å–ø–æ–ª—å–∑–æ–≤–∞–ª–∏ –ª–∏–º–∏—Ç —Ä–∞–∑—Ä–µ—à–µ–Ω–Ω—ã—Ö –¥–Ω–µ–π.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>–ú–æ–∂–Ω–æ –ª–∏ –ø—É—Ç–µ—à–µ—Å—Ç–≤–æ–≤–∞—Ç—å, –µ—Å–ª–∏ –ø—Ä–æ—Ü–µ–¥—É—Ä–∞ –ª–µ–≥–∞–ª–∏–∑–∞—Ü–∏–∏ –≤ –ü–æ–ª—å—à–µ –Ω–µ –∑–∞–∫–æ–Ω—á–∏–ª–∞—Å—å (–∫–∞—Ä—Ç–∞ –ø–æ–±—ã—Ç—É), –Ω–æ –≤ –ø–∞—Å–ø–æ—Ä—Ç–µ –ø–æ—Å—Ç–∞–≤–ª–µ–Ω–∞ ‚Äã‚Äã–ø–µ—á–∞—Ç—å?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>–°–æ–≥–ª–∞—Å–Ω–æ —Å—Ç. 108 –ó–∞–∫–æ–Ω–∞ –æ–± –∏–Ω–æ—Å—Ç—Ä–∞–Ω—Ü–∞—Ö –æ—Ç 12 –¥–µ–∫–∞–±—Ä—è 2013 –≥–æ–¥–∞, –ø—Ä–µ–±—ã–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ –∏–Ω–æ—Å—Ç—Ä–∞–Ω—Ü–∞ –≤ –ü–æ–ª—å—à–µ —Å—á–∏—Ç–∞–µ—Ç—Å—è –∑–∞–∫–æ–Ω–Ω—ã–º —Å –¥–∞—Ç—ã –ø–æ–¥–∞—á–∏ –∑–∞—è–≤–ª–µ–Ω–∏—è –Ω–∞ –≤–∏–¥ –Ω–∞ –∂–∏—Ç–µ–ª—å—Å—Ç–≤–æ. –ü–æ–¥—Ç–≤–µ—Ä–∂–¥–µ–Ω–∏–µ–º –æ –ø—Ä–µ–¥–æ—Å—Ç–∞–≤–ª–µ–Ω–∏–∏ –∫–æ–º–ø–ª–µ–∫—Ç–∞ –¥–æ–∫—É–º–µ–Ω—Ç–æ–≤ —è–≤–ª—è–µ—Ç—Å—è —à—Ç–∞–º–ø, –∫–æ—Ç–æ—Ä—ã–π —Å—Ç–∞–≤–∏—Ç—Å—è –≤ –ø—Ä–æ–µ–∑–¥–Ω–æ–π –¥–æ–∫—É–º–µ–Ω—Ç (–ø–∞—Å–ø–æ—Ä—Ç). –ï—Å–ª–∏ —É –≤–∞—Å –µ—Å—Ç—å –¥–µ–π—Å—Ç–≤—É—é—â–∞—è –≤–∏–∑–∞ –∏–ª–∏ –≤–∏–¥ –Ω–∞ –∂–∏—Ç–µ–ª—å—Å—Ç–≤–æ –∏–ª–∏ –±–∏–æ–º–µ—Ç—Ä–∏—á–µ—Å–∫–∏–π –ø–∞—Å–ø–æ—Ä—Ç –∏ –Ω–µ–∏—Å–ø–æ–ª—å–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–Ω—ã–µ –¥–Ω–∏ –±–µ–∑–≤–∏–∑–∞ –ø–æ—Å–ª–µ –ø–æ–¥–∞—á–∏ –¥–æ–∫—É–º–µ–Ω—Ç–æ–≤, –≤—ã –º–æ–∂–µ—Ç–µ –ø—É—Ç–µ—à–µ—Å—Ç–≤–æ–≤–∞—Ç—å. –ï—Å–ª–∏ –ø—Ä–∏—á–∏–Ω—ã –ø—Ä–µ–±—ã–≤–∞–Ω–∏—è –≤ –ü–æ–ª—å—à–µ, —É–ø–æ–º—è–Ω—É—Ç—ã–µ –≤—ã—à–µ, –±–æ–ª–µ–µ –Ω–µ –¥–µ–π—Å—Ç–≤–∏—Ç–µ–ª—å–Ω—ã, –≤—ã –º–æ–∂–µ—Ç–µ —Å–ø–æ–∫–æ–π–Ω–æ –Ω–∞—Ö–æ–¥–∏—Ç—å—Å—è –≤ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞–Ω–µ –≤ –æ–∂–∏–¥–∞–Ω–∏–∏ —Ä–µ—à–µ–Ω–∏—è –æ –≤—ã–¥–∞—á–µ –∫–∞—Ä—Ç—ã –ø–æ–±—ã—Ç—É. –ë–æ–ª–µ–µ —Ç–æ–≥–æ, –ø–µ—á–∞—Ç—å –¥–∞–µ—Ç –≤–∞–º –ø—Ä–∞–≤–æ —Å–ø–æ–∫–æ–π–Ω–æ –≤–µ—Ä–Ω—É—Ç—å—Å—è –≤ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞–Ω—É –ø—Ä–æ–∏—Å—Ö–æ–∂–¥–µ–Ω–∏—è –¥–æ –∑–∞–≤–µ—Ä—à–µ–Ω–∏—è –ø—Ä–æ—Ü–µ–¥—É—Ä—ã –ª–µ–≥–∞–ª–∏–∑–∞—Ü–∏–∏. –ü—Ä–∞–≤–¥–∞, —à—Ç–∞–º–ø –Ω–µ –¥–∞–µ—Ç –≤–∞–º –ø—Ä–∞–≤–∞ –ø–µ—Ä–µ—Å–µ–∫–∞—Ç—å —à–µ–Ω–≥–µ–Ω—Å–∫—É—é –≥—Ä–∞–Ω–∏—Ü—É, —Ç–æ –µ—Å—Ç—å –≤—ä–µ—Ö–∞—Ç—å –≤ –ü–æ–ª—å—à—É –æ–±—Ä–∞—Ç–Ω–æ –≤—ã —Å–º–æ–∂–µ—Ç–µ —Ç–æ–ª—å–∫–æ –ø–æ—Å–ª–µ –ø–æ–ª—É—á–µ–Ω–∏—è –≤–∏–∑—ã.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>–ú–æ–∂–Ω–æ –ª–∏ –ø–æ–º–µ–Ω—è—Ç—å –º–µ—Å—Ç–æ —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç—ã –∏ —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–æ–¥–∞—Ç–µ–ª—è –≤ –ø—Ä–æ—Ü–µ—Å—Å–µ –ª–µ–≥–∞–ª–∏–∑–∞—Ü–∏–∏ –≤ –ü–æ–ª—å—à–µ?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>–î–∞, –∫–æ–Ω–µ—á–Ω–æ. –ï—Å–ª–∏ –≤–∞—à–∞ —Ü–µ–ª—å –ø—Ä–µ–±—ã–≤–∞–Ω–∏—è –≤ –ü–æ–ª—å—à–µ ‚Äî —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–∞—Ç—å, –Ω–æ –≤—ã —Ö–æ—Ç–∏—Ç–µ —Å–º–µ–Ω–∏—Ç—å —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–æ–¥–∞—Ç–µ–ª—è, –∞ –ø—Ä–æ—Ü–µ—Å—Å –ª–µ–≥–∞–ª–∏–∑–∞—Ü–∏–∏ –µ—â–µ –Ω–µ –∑–∞–≤–µ—Ä—à–µ–Ω, ‚Äî –≤—ã –º–æ–∂–µ—Ç–µ —ç—Ç–æ —Å–¥–µ–ª–∞—Ç—å. –ù–µ–æ–±—Ö–æ–¥–∏–º–æ –Ω–∞–ø–∏—Å–∞—Ç—å –∑–∞—è–≤–ª–µ–Ω–∏–µ –æ —Å–º–µ–Ω–µ —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–æ–¥–∞—Ç–µ–ª—è, —Å–æ–±—Ä–∞—Ç—å –≤—Å–µ –Ω–µ–æ–±—Ö–æ–¥–∏–º—ã–µ –¥–æ–∫—É–º–µ–Ω—Ç—ã —É –Ω–æ–≤–æ–≥–æ —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–æ–¥–∞—Ç–µ–ª—è –∏ –ø–µ—Ä–µ–¥–∞—Ç—å –∏—Ö –≤ —Å–æ–æ—Ç–≤–µ—Ç—Å—Ç–≤—É—é—â–∏–π –≤–æ–µ–≤–æ–¥—Å–∫–∏–π —É–∂–æ–Ω–¥. –¢.–µ. –≤ —É–∂–æ–Ω–¥ –≤—ã –¥–æ–ª–∂–Ω—ã –ø—Ä–∏–Ω–µ—Å—Ç–∏ –Ω–æ–≤—ã–π –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç –¥–æ–∫—É–º–µ–Ω—Ç–æ–≤, –∫–æ—Ç–æ—Ä—ã–π –æ—Ç–Ω–æ—Å–∏—Ç—Å—è –∫ –Ω–æ–≤–æ–º—É –º–µ—Å—Ç—É —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç—ã.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>–ß—Ç–æ –¥–µ–ª–∞—Ç—å, –µ—Å–ª–∏ —Ö–æ—á–µ—à—å –ø–æ–º–µ–Ω—è—Ç—å —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–æ–¥–∞—Ç–µ–ª—è –ø–æ—Å–ª–µ –ø–æ–ª—É—á–µ–Ω–∏—è –≤–∏–¥–∞ –Ω–∞ –∂–∏—Ç–µ–ª—å—Å—Ç–≤–æ?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>–í —Ä–µ—à–µ–Ω–∏–∏ –æ –ø—Ä–µ–¥–æ—Å—Ç–∞–≤–ª–µ–Ω–∏–∏ –∫–∞—Ä—Ç—ã –ø–æ–±—ã—Ç—É –ø–æ —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–µ –≤–ø–∏—Å—ã–≤–∞—é—Ç—Å—è –¥–∞–Ω–Ω—ã–µ –æ —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–æ–¥–∞—Ç–µ–ª–µ, —É–∫–∞–∑—ã–≤–∞–µ—Ç—Å—è, –∫–∞–∫—É—é —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç—É –±—É–¥–µ—Ç –≤—ã–ø–æ–ª–Ω—è—Ç—å –∏–Ω–æ—Å—Ç—Ä–∞–Ω–µ—Ü, –æ–±—ä–µ–º —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç—ã –∏ —Ä–∞–∑–º–µ—Ä –∑–∞—Ä–ø–ª–∞—Ç—ã. –í –¥–∞–Ω–Ω–æ–º —Å–ª—É—á–∞–µ –ø—Ä–∏ —Å–º–µ–Ω–µ —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–æ–¥–∞—Ç–µ–ª—è –≤—ã –æ–±—è–∑–∞–Ω—ã –ø–æ–¥–∞—Ç—å –¥–æ–∫—É–º–µ–Ω—Ç—ã –Ω–∞ –∫–∞—Ä—Ç—É –ø–æ–±—ã—Ç—É —Å–Ω–æ–≤–∞.&nbsp;<strong>–ë–æ–ª–µ–µ —Ç–æ–≥–æ: –µ—Å–ª–∏ –≤—ã –ø–æ—Ç–µ—Ä—è–µ—Ç–µ —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç—É, –Ω–∞ —Ç–æ, —á—Ç–æ–±—ã —É–≤–µ–¥–æ–º–∏—Ç—å –º–µ—Å—Ç–Ω—ã–π —É–∂–æ–Ω–¥, —É –≤–∞—Å –µ—Å—Ç—å 15 –¥–Ω–µ–π, –∞ –Ω–∞ –ø–æ–∏—Å–∫–∏ –Ω–æ–≤–æ–π —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç—ã 30 –¥–Ω–µ–π.&nbsp;</strong>–ó–∞ —ç—Ç–æ –≤—Ä–µ–º—è –≤—ã –¥–æ–ª–∂–Ω—ã –Ω–µ —Ç–æ–ª—å–∫–æ –Ω–∞–π—Ç–∏ –Ω–æ–≤–æ–≥–æ —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–æ–¥–∞—Ç–µ–ª—è, –Ω–æ –∏ —Å–æ–±—Ä–∞—Ç—å –Ω–æ–≤—ã–π –ø–∞–∫–µ—Ç –¥–æ–∫—É–º–µ–Ω—Ç–æ–≤ –¥–ª—è –ª–µ–≥–∞–ª–∏–∑–∞—Ü–∏–∏ –≤ –ü–æ–ª—å—à–µ. –ù–µ–≤—ã–ø–æ–ª–Ω–µ–Ω–∏–µ —ç—Ç–æ–≥–æ –æ–±—è–∑–∞—Ç–µ–ª—å—Å—Ç–≤–∞ –º–æ–∂–µ—Ç –æ—Ç—Ä–∏—Ü–∞—Ç–µ–ª—å–Ω–æ –ø–æ–≤–ª–∏—è—Ç—å –Ω–∞ –ø–æ—Å–ª–µ–¥—É—é—â–∏–µ –ø–æ–ø—ã—Ç–∫–∏ –ø–æ–ª—É—á–∏—Ç—å –∫–∞—Ä—Ç—É –ø–æ–±—ã—Ç—É. –ï—Å–ª–∏ –∏–Ω–æ—Å—Ç—Ä–∞–Ω–µ—Ü –ø–æ–ª—É—á–∏–ª –≤–∏–¥ –Ω–∞ –∂–∏—Ç–µ–ª—å—Å—Ç–≤–æ –ø–æ –∫–æ—Ç–æ—Ä–æ–º—É –Ω–µ –Ω—É–∂–Ω—ã —Ä–∞–∑—Ä–µ—à–µ–Ω–∏—è –Ω–∞ —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç—É, –º–æ–∂–Ω–æ –º–µ–Ω—è—Ç—å —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–æ–¥–∞—Ç–µ–ª—è —Å–∫–æ–ª—å–∫–æ —É–≥–æ–¥–Ω–æ –±–µ–∑ —É–≤–µ–¥–æ–º–ª–µ–Ω–∏—è —É–∂–æ–Ω–¥–∞ –∏ –∑–∞–º–µ–Ω—ã –∫–∞—Ä—Ç—ã –ø–æ–±—ã—Ç—É.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '–õ–µ–≥–∞–ª–∏–∑–∞—Ü–∏—è –≤ –ü–æ–ª—å—à–µ: –æ—Ç–≤–µ—Ç—ã –Ω–∞ —á–∞—Å—Ç–æ –∑–∞–¥–∞–≤–∞–µ–º—ã–µ –≤–æ–ø—Ä–æ—Å—ã', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '333-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-02-18 16:48:19', '2020-02-18 13:48:19', '', 333, 'http://blessed-firm.com/2020/02/18/333-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(336, 1, '2020-02-18 16:48:19', '2020-02-18 13:48:19', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Every day, dozens of foreigners turn to migrant counselling centres in Poland with numerous questions about legalization in Poland. We collected the most popular ones and published them along with the answers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What is the right way to count the days used during the visa-free stay?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Visa-free stay in Poland is short-term and amounts to no more than 90 out of 180 days. In practice, it looks like this: border guards count the days of your stay for the last 180 days. If you have had 90 days between trips to the Schengen countries, you do not need to count 180 days - after this break you are again entitled to stay in the Schengen area for 90 days. It should be remembered: when calculating the previous days of short stay, all days of stay on the basis of a C visa, D visa and residence permit are taken into account if you have been to a different Schengen country than the one in which the documents were issued.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Is it possible to stay in Poland without compulsory travel to a country of origin on a visa-free stay with a biometric passport after the expiration of the Polish type D visa?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yes. If the Polish entry document was a Polish national type D visa, and if you have a biometric passport, you can extend your stay in Poland under the visa-free regime, provided that you have not yet used the limit of permitted days.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Is it possible to travel if the legalization procedure in Poland is not over (the map is used), but the passport is stamped?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>According to Art. 108 Aliens Act of December 12, 2013, a foreigner&#39;s stay in Poland is considered legal from the date of application for residence. Confirmation of the provision of a set of documents is a stamp, which is put in the travel document (passport). If you have a valid visa or residence permit or biometric passport and unused visa-free days after filing your documents, you can travel. If the reasons for staying in Poland mentioned above are no longer valid, you can safely stay in the country awaiting a decision to issue a card. Moreover, the seal gives you the right to return safely to your country of origin until the legalization procedure is complete. However, the stamp does not give you the right to cross the Schengen border, that is, you can enter Poland back only after obtaining a visa.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Is it possible to change the place of work and employer in the process of legalization in Poland?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yes of course. If your goal of staying in Poland is to work, but you want to change employers, and the legalization process is not yet complete, you can do so. It is necessary to write an application for a change of employer, to collect all the necessary documents from the new employer and to transfer them to the appropriate governor&#39;s office. I.e. you have to bring a new package of documents that applies to the new place of work.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What if you want to change your employer after receiving a residence permit?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The decision to provide a card to the employee&#39;s job includes data about the employer, indicates what kind of work the foreigner will do, the amount of work and the size of the salary. In this case, when you change your employer, you are required to apply for a card again.¬†<strong>What&#39;s more, if you lose your job, you have 15 days to notify your local job, and 30 days to find a new job.¬†</strong>During this time you must not only find a new employer, but also collect a new package of documents for legalization in Poland. Failure to do so may adversely affect subsequent attempts to obtain a card. If a foreigner has obtained a residence permit for which you do not need a work permit, you can change the employer as much as you want without notifying the person and replacement of the card.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Legalization in Poland: answers to frequently asked questions', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '%d0%bb%d0%b5%d0%b0%b3%d0%b0%d0%b8%d0%b7%b0%d1%86%d0%b8%d1%8f-%d0%b0%b2-%d0%bf%d0%be%d0%bb%d1%8c%d1%88%d0%b5-%d0%be%d1%82%d0%b2%d0%b5%d1%82%d1%8b-%d0-bd%d0%b0%d1%87%d0-b0%d1%81%d1%82%d0%be-%d0%b7', '', '', '2020-02-18 16:48:19', '2020-02-18 13:48:19', '', 0, 'http://blessed-firm.com/?p=333', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(337, 1, '2020-02-18 16:48:19', '2020-02-18 13:48:19', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ka≈ºdego dnia dziesiƒÖtki obcokrajowc√≥w zwracajƒÖ siƒô do o≈õrodk√≥w doradztwa dla migrant√≥w w Polsce z licznymi pytaniami o legalizacjƒô w Polsce. Zebrali≈õmy najpopularniejsze i opublikowali≈õmy je wraz z odpowiedziami.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Jaki jest w≈Ça≈õciwy spos√≥b liczenia dni u≈ºywanych podczas bezwizowego pobytu?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Pobyt bezwizowy w Polsce jest kr√≥tkoterminowy i wynosi nie wiƒôcej ni≈º 90 na 180 dni. W praktyce wyglƒÖda to tak: stra≈º graniczna liczy dni pobytu przez ostatnie 180 dni. Je≈õli mia≈Çe≈õ 90 dni miƒôdzy podr√≥≈ºami do kraj√≥w Strefy Schengen, nie musisz liczyƒá 180 dni - po tej przerwie masz ponownie prawo do pozostania w strefie Schengen przez 90 dni. Nale≈ºy pamiƒôtaƒá: przy obliczaniu poprzednich dni kr√≥tkiego pobytu, wszystkie dni pobytu na podstawie wizy C, wizy D i zezwolenia na pobyt sƒÖ brane pod uwagƒô, je≈õli by≈Çe≈õ w innym kraju Schengen ni≈º ten, w kt√≥rym dokumenty zosta≈Çy wydane.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Czy po wyga≈õniƒôciu polskiej wizy typu D mo≈ºliwe jest pozostanie w Polsce bez obowiƒÖzkowej podr√≥≈ºy do kraju pochodzenia na bezwizowym podaniu paszportu biometrycznego?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tak. Je≈õli polski dokument wjazdu by≈Ç polskƒÖ krajowƒÖ wizƒÖ typu D, a paszport biometryczny mo≈ºe zostaƒá przed≈Çu≈ºony w Polsce w ramach ruchu bezwizowego, pod warunkiem, ≈ºe nie skorzysta≈Çe≈õ jeszcze z limitu dozwolonych dni.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Czy mo≈ºna podr√≥≈ºowaƒá, je≈õli procedura legalizacji w Polsce siƒô nie sko≈Ñczy≈Ça (mapa jest u≈ºywana), ale paszport jest ostemplowany?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Zgodnie z art. 108 Ustawa o cudzoziemcach z dnia 12 grudnia 2013 r., pobyt cudzoziemca w Polsce jest uwa≈ºany za legalny od dnia z≈Ço≈ºenia wniosku o pobyt. Potwierdzenie m.in. Je≈õli masz wa≈ºnƒÖ wizƒô lub zezwolenie na pobyt lub paszport biometryczny i niewykorzystane dni bezwizowe po z≈Ço≈ºeniu dokument√≥w, mo≈ºesz podr√≥≈ºowaƒá. Je≈õli powody pobytu w Polsce, o kt√≥rych mowa powy≈ºej, nie sƒÖ ju≈º aktualne, mo≈ºesz bezpiecznie pozostaƒá w kraju w oczekiwaniu na decyzjƒô o wystawieniu karty. Co wiƒôcej, pieczƒôƒá daje ci prawo do bezpiecznego powrotu do kraju pochodzenia do czasu zako≈Ñczenia procedury legalizacji. Jednak pieczƒôƒá nie daje prawa do przekroczenia granicy Schengen, to znaczy, ≈ºe mo≈ºna wjechaƒá do Polski z powrotem dopiero po uzyskaniu wizy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Czy mo≈ºliwe jest zmiana miejsca pracy i pracodawcy w procesie legalizacji w Polsce?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tak oczywi≈õcie. Je≈õli twoim celem jest pozostanie w Polsce, ale chcesz zmieniƒá pracodawcƒô, a proces legalizacji nie jest jeszcze zako≈Ñczony, mo≈ºesz to zrobiƒá. Konieczne jest napisanie wniosku o zmianƒô pracodawcy, zebranie wszystkich niezbƒôdnych dokument√≥w od nowego pracodawcy i przeniesienie ich do odpowiedniego urzƒôdu gubernatora. Ie. musisz przynie≈õƒá nowy pakiet dokument√≥w, kt√≥ry ma zastosowanie do nowego miejsca pracy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Co zrobiƒá, je≈õli chcesz zmieniƒá pracodawcƒô po otrzymaniu zezwolenia na pobyt?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Decyzja o przekazaniu karty do pracy pracownika zawiera dane o pracodawcy, wskazuje, jaki rodzaj pracy zrobi cudzoziemiec, ilo≈õƒá pracy i wielko≈õƒá wynagrodzenia. W takim przypadku, gdy zmienisz pracodawcƒô, musisz ponownie ubiegaƒá siƒô o kartƒô.¬†<strong>Co wiƒôcej, je≈õli stracisz pracƒô, masz 15 dni na powiadomienie lokalnej pracy i 30 dni na znalezienie nowej pracy.¬†</strong>W tym czasie trzeba nie tylko znale≈∫ƒá nowego pracodawcƒô, ale tak≈ºe zebraƒá nowy pakiet dokument√≥w do legalizacji w Polsce. Niezastosowanie siƒô do tego mo≈ºe niekorzystnie wp≈ÇynƒÖƒá na kolejne pr√≥by uzyskania karty. Je≈õli cudzoziemiec uzyska≈Ç zezwolenie na pobyt, dla kt√≥rego nie potrzebujesz pozwolenia na pracƒô, mo≈ºesz zmieniƒá pracodawcƒô tak bardzo, jak chcesz, bez powiadamiania osoby i wymiany karty.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Legalizacja w Polsce: odpowiedzi na czƒôsto zadawane pytania', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '%d0%bb%d0%b5%d0%b0%b3%d0%b0%d0%b8%d0%b7%b0%d1%86%d0%b8%d1%8f-%d0%b0%b2-%d0%bf%d0%be%be%be%d0%bb%d1%8c%d1%88%d0%b5-%d0%be%d1%82%d0%b2%d0%b5%d1%82%d1%8b-%d0-bd%d0%b0%d1%87%d0-b0%d1%81%d1%82%d0%be-%d0%b7', '', '', '2020-02-18 16:48:19', '2020-02-18 13:48:19', '', 0, 'http://blessed-firm.com/?p=333', 0, 'post', '', 0),
