wskie Centrum EXPO XXI, przy ul. Ignacego PrƒÖdzy≈Ñskiego 12/14 oraz PGE Stadion Narodowy, al. Ksiƒôcia J√≥zefa Poniatowskiego 1 w Warszawie</li>\r\n 	<li>wojew√≥dztwo opolskie: Centrum Wystawienniczo-Kongresowe, przy ul. Wroc≈Çawskiej 158 w Opolu,</li>\r\n 	<li>wojew√≥dztwo podkarpackie: SP ZOZ MSWiA, przy ul. ul. Krakowskiej 16 w Rzeszowie,</li>\r\n 	<li>wojew√≥dztwo podlaskie: Hala sportowa Uniwersytetu Medycznego, przy ul. Micha≈Ça Wo≈Çodyjowskiego 1 oraz budynek E1 Uniwersyteckiego Szpitala Klinicznego, przy ul. ≈ªurawiej 14 w Bia≈Çymstoku,</li>\r\n 	<li>wojew√≥dztwo pomorskie: Sanatorium MSWiA, przy ul. Bitwy pod P≈Çowcami 63-65 w Sopocie,</li>\r\n 	<li>wojew√≥dztwo ≈õlƒÖskie: Miƒôdzynarodowe Centrum Kongresowe, pl. S≈Çawika i Antalla 1 w Katowicach,</li>\r\n 	<li>wojew√≥dztwo ≈õwiƒôtokrzyskie: Targi Kielce SA, przy ul. Zak≈Çadowej 1 w Kielcach,</li>\r\n 	<li>wojew√≥dztwo warmi≈Ñsko-mazurskie: Zesp√≥≈Ç Opieki Zdrowotnej, przy ul. Mickiewicza 25 w Nidzicy oraz Zesp√≥≈Ç Opieki Zdrowotnej, przy ul. Marii Sk≈Çodowskiej-Curie 12 w Szczytnie,</li>\r\n 	<li>wojew√≥dztwo wielkopolskie: Miƒôdzynarodowe Targi Pozna≈Ñskie, przy ul. G≈Çogowskiej 14 w Poznaniu,</li>\r\n 	<li>wojew√≥dztwo zachodniopomorskie: NETTO ARENA, przy ul. W≈Çadys≈Çawa Szafera 3/5/7 oraz Samodzielny Publiczny Szpital Kliniczny nr 2, przy al. Powsta≈Ñc√≥w Wielkopolskich 72 w Szczecinie.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Dbamy o naszych senior√≥w</strong>\r\n\r\nSeniorzy to grupa najbardziej nara≈ºona w sytuacji zaka≈ºenia koronawirusem. Dlatego wprowadzamy rozwiƒÖzania, kt√≥re pomogƒÖ nam chroniƒá naszych rodzic√≥w, czy dziadk√≥w.\r\n\r\n<strong>Seniorze zosta≈Ñ w domu i skorzystaj ze specjalnej infolinii - 22 505 11 11</strong>\r\n\r\nW ostatnich dniach uruchomili≈õmy Solidarno≈õciowy Korpus Wsparcia Senior√≥w. Jednym z filar√≥w tego projektu jest dedykowana infolinia dla os√≥b powy≈ºej 70. roku ≈ºycia. Do tej pory skorzysta≈Ço z niej ju≈º blisko 8 tys. os√≥b. Celem infolinii jest wsparcie senior√≥w w codziennych czynno≈õciach, kt√≥re wymagajƒÖ wyj≈õcia z domu ‚Äì przede wszystkim w zrobieniu zakup√≥w.\r\n\r\nWszystkie osoby, kt√≥ry chcia≈Çyby w≈ÇƒÖczyƒá siƒô w akcjƒô #WspierajSeniora, mogƒÖ to zrobiƒá za pomocƒÖ strony internetowej¬†<a href=\"http://www.wspierajseniora.pl/\">www.wspierajseniora.pl</a>. Do tej pory chƒôƒá niesienia pomocy zadeklarowa≈Ço blisko 6 tys. wolontariuszy z ca≈Çego kraju!\r\n\r\n<strong>Dodatkowe ≈õrodki dla dom√≥w pomocy spo≈Çecznej</strong>\r\n\r\nW pa≈∫dzierniku uruchomili≈õmy 38 mln z≈Ç z bud≈ºetu pa≈Ñstwa na przygotowanie i zabezpieczenie DPS-√≥w przed wzrostem zaka≈ºe≈Ñ koronawirusem w okresie jesiennym. A≈º 328 mln z≈Ç z Europejskiego Funduszu Spo≈Çecznego oraz bud≈ºetu pa≈Ñstwa trafia do dom√≥w pomocy spo≈Çecznej na bie≈ºƒÖce potrzeby zwiƒÖzane z epidemiƒÖ koronawirusa. Za codzienne po≈õwiƒôcenie i zaanga≈ºowanie w wykonywane obowiƒÖzki, pracownicy DPS-√≥w mogƒÖ r√≥wnie≈º liczyƒá na dodatki do wynagrodzenia.\r\n\r\n<strong>Tarcza Antykryzysowa chroni przed kryzysem polskich przedsiƒôbiorc√≥w</strong>\r\n\r\nChronimy firmy oraz miliony miejsc pracy przed skutkami koronawirusa. Naszym celem jest zapewnienie pracownikom stabilno≈õci zatrudnienia, a firmom ‚Äì mo≈ºliwo≈õci rozwoju. Skuteczno≈õƒá naszych dzia≈Ça≈Ñ potwierdzajƒÖ dane. Do polskich firm trafi≈Ço ju≈º ponad 148 mld z≈Ç w ramach Tarczy Antykryzysowej i Tarczy Finansowej.\r\n\r\nW tym trudnym okresie wspieramy tak≈ºe bran≈ºƒô turystycznƒÖ. Do tej pory w ca≈Çym kraju zosta≈Ço przyznanych ju≈º ponad 1 mln bon√≥w turystycznych o warto≈õci 914 mln z≈Ç. Polskie rodziny dokona≈Çy ju≈º 318 tys. p≈Çatno≈õci bonem turystycznym na kwotƒô 232 mln z≈Ç.\r\n\r\n<strong>Wsp√≥≈Çpraca ponad podzia≈Çami</strong>\r\n\r\nPremier Mateusz Morawiecki ponownie spotka≈Ç siƒô z przedstawicielami opozycji oraz prezydentami najwiƒôkszych miast. Rozmowy dotyczy≈Çy s≈Çu≈ºby zdrowia oraz dzia≈Ça≈Ñ podejmowanych w ramach walki z epidemiƒÖ koronawirusa. To nie pierwsze tego typu spotkanie cz≈Çonk√≥w rzƒÖdu z opozycjƒÖ. Odbywa≈Çy siƒô ju≈º konsultacje z przedstawicielami klub√≥w parlamentarnych w kwestiach zwiƒÖzanych z trudnƒÖ sytuacjƒÖ na Bia≈Çorusi. Jeste≈õmy otwarci na dialog. Epidemia koronawirusa to dla wszystkich test solidarno≈õci spo≈Çecznej, a tak≈ºe umiejƒôtno≈õci pracy ponad podzia≈Çami.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Poszerzamy strategiƒô walki z koronawirusem', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '863-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-11-04 16:21:39', '2020-11-04 13:21:39', '', 863, 'https://blessedfirm.com/blog/2020/11/04/863-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(867, 1, '2020-11-04 16:21:39', '2020-11-04 13:21:39', 'The health and safety of citizens is of the utmost importance to us. We are taking further steps to make the fight against coronavirus more effective. We\'re accelerating testing of patients with suspected covid-19. For this purpose, we will use antigen tests, the result of which is known after a few minutes. The health status of people who do not have symptoms or are mild will be monitored with a pulse oximeter-all to relieve the burden on hospitals and medical facilities. We appreciate the work of the medical services-we grant additional benefits to doctors, nurses, laboratory diagnosticians and rescuers and increase their maximum amount.\r\n\r\nExpanded coronavirus strategy\r\nExpanding coronavirus strategy-what will change?\r\nThe pulse oximeter will monitor your health at home\r\n\r\nA pulse oximeter is a small electronic device. It is used for non-invasive measurement of blood saturation. It will soon assist the medical services in monitoring the health status of COVID-19 patients who are experiencing the disease in a mild manner and have been qualified for home medical care. The data transmitted by the device will be analyzed by a special monitoring center. This will be a new unit, which will be appointed by the Ministry of health.\r\n\r\nThe result even in a few minutes thanks to antigen tests\r\n\r\nUntil now, the main test used to confirm coronavirus infection has been PCR. In order for testing to go faster, we will also use antigen tests more often than before. This test can detect the presence of viral protein in patients with high numbers of viral particles in the airway epithelium. The test result is already known from 10 to 30 min.\r\n\r\nLarger insulator base\r\n\r\nAn isolation ward is a place where people infected with coronavirus recover. Patients who cannot be isolated in their own home-for example, because they live with people from the high-risk group-are referred to insulators. There are also patients who were in the hospital, but their condition is good enough that they can continue treatment in the isolation ward.\r\n\r\nSo far, we\'ve had 6,500 available in the isolation wards. beds. We\'ll increase the number to 10,000. in 55 facilities throughout Poland.\r\n\r\nAdditional benefits for medical services\r\n\r\nWe appreciate and are grateful to the medical services for their daily work. We pay an additional benefit for medical personnel who are involved in the fight against covid-19. More than 30,000 so far. people from the medical staff were in quarantine. After this decision, the medical staff will not be quarantined, thanks to the daily antigen tests \" - said the head of the kprm Micha≈Ç Dworczyk.\r\n\r\nHospital at PGE National ‚Äì the first stage of work is coming to an end\r\n\r\nThe first phase of the construction of the hospital at PGE national is coming to an end. All electrical and oxygen work has been completed. Finishing and cleaning works are currently underway. As part of the hospital are already ready m.in:\r\n\r\npatient\'s emergency room,\r\nsick room equipped with 285 beds of which 16 are intended for intensive care,\r\nIntensive Surveillance Unit,\r\ntreatment room,\r\nimaging laboratories equipped with 4 mobile X-ray machines and tomograph,\r\nhospital pharmacy department,\r\nmedicine room.\r\nThe temporary hospital at the PGE national stadium will be equipped with 160 cardiomonitors, 45 respirators, 4 mobile X-rays, 3 oxygen generators, 2 ultrasounds. In addition, in 45 km of electrical wires and 5 km of copper tubes to oxygen.\r\n\r\nAt this stage, the hospital has 300 beds available. We are starting work on the second stage-after its completion, the number of beds will increase from 300 to 500. On November 16, another temporary hospital will start operating in Warsaw-the EXPO XXI center in Warsaw.\r\n\r\nTemporary hospital in every voivodship\r\n\r\nThe temporary hospital, which is being built at the PGE national stadium, will not be the only such facility in the country. At least one hospital for COVID-19 patients will be established in each province. Most of them will be put into operation between 15 and 30 November. Thanks to these actions, the base of hospital beds for patients infected with coronavirus will increase by more than 5 thousand. places.\r\n\r\nMost temporary hospitals will be built in convention and exhibition centers and sports halls. These will not be facilities that are currently used by the health service. The cost of adaptation of objects (not including equipment) will be about 130 million rubles.\r\n\r\nFind out where to build a hospital in your province:\r\n\r\nvoivodship dolno≈õlƒÖskie: Terminal Hotel Centrum Konferencyjne, at UL. Rakietowa 33 in Wroc≈Çaw,\r\nvoivodship kujawsko-pomorskie: 22. Military Hospital SP ZOZ at UL. Wojska Polskiego 5 in Ciechocin,\r\nvoivodship lubelskie: Targi Lublin S. A., at UL. Dworcowa 11 in Lublin\r\nlubuskie Voivodeship: Centre for Maternal and Child Health, at Zyty 26 in Zielona G√≥ra,\r\n≈Ç√≥d≈∫ Voivodeship: EXPO-≈Å√ìD≈π Sp√≥≈Çka z o. o., at UL. Politechniki 4 in ≈Ç√≥d≈∫,\r\nvoivodship ma≈Çopolskie: Trauma Centre For Emergency Medicine and catastrophes at UL. Miko≈Çaja Kopernika 50 and EXPO Krak√≥w at UL. Galicyjska 9 in Krak√≥w,\r\nmazowieckie Voivodeship: Warsaw Expo XXI Centre, at Ignacy PrƒÖdzy≈Ñski 12/14 and PGE National Stadium, Prince J√≥zef Poniatowski Avenue 1 in Warsaw\r\nOpole Voivodeship: exhibition and Congress Centre, 158 Wroc≈Çawska Street, Opole,\r\nvoivodship podkarpackie: SP ZOZ MSWiA, at ul. ul. Krakowska 16 in Rzesz√≥w,\r\npodlaskie Voivodeship: Sports Hall of the Medical University, 1 Micha≈Ç Wo≈Çodyjowski Street and building E1 of the University Clinical Hospital, 14 ≈ªurawiej Street in Bia≈Çystok,\r\nPomeranian Voivodeship: Sanatorium MSWiA, 63-65 Bitwy pod P≈Çowcami Street in Sopot,\r\nSilesian Voivodeship: International Congress Centre, s≈Çawika and Antalla square 1 in Katowice,\r\nvoivodship ≈õwiƒôtokrzyskie: Targi Kielce SA, at UL. Zak≈Çadowa 1 in Kielce,\r\nvoivodship warmi≈Ñsko-mazurskie: Health Care Unit, at UL. Mickiewicza 25 in Nidzica and Health Care Unit, at UL. Maria Sk≈Çodowska-Curie 12 in Szczytno,\r\nvoivodship wielkopolskie: Pozna≈Ñ International Fair, at 14 G≈Çogowska Street in Pozna≈Ñ,\r\nvoivodship zachodniopomorskie: Netto arena, ul.w≈Çadys≈Çawa szafera 3/5/7 and independent public Clinical Hospital No. 2, al. Powsta≈Ñc√≥w wielkopolskich 72 in Szczecin.\r\nWe care about our seniors\r\n\r\nThe elderly are the most vulnerable group to coronavirus infection. That is why we are introducing solutions that will help us protect our parents or grandparents.\r\n\r\nSenior stay at home and use the special hotline - 22 505 11 11\r\n\r\nIn recent days, we have launched a Solidarity Corps to support seniors. One of the pillars of this project is a dedicated helpline for people over 70. one year old. So far, nearly 8 thousand have used it. persons. The aim of the helpline is to support seniors in everyday activities that require leaving home-especially shopping.\r\n\r\nAll persons who would like to participate in the #Supportsenior campaign can do so via the website www.wspierajseniora.pl.to date, the desire to help declared nearly 6 thousand. volunteers from all over the country!\r\n\r\nAdditional measures for social welfare homes\r\n\r\nIn October, we mobilized PLN 38 million from the state budget for the preparation and protection of DPS against an increase in coronavirus infections in the autumn period. As much as PLN 328 million from the European Social Fund and the state budget goes to social assistance homes for current needs related to the coronavirus epidemic. For the daily sacrifice and commitment to the duties performed, DPS employees can also count on salary supplements.\r\n\r\nAnti-crisis shield protects Polish entrepreneurs from crisis\r\n\r\nWe protect businesses and millions of jobs from the coronavirus. Our goal is to provide employees with stable employment, and companies-opportunities for development. The effectiveness of our actions is confirmed by the data. Polish companies have already received more than PLN 148 billion under the anti-crisis and financial shield.\r\n\r\nWe are also supporting the tourism industry during this difficult period. To date, more than 1 million tourist vouchers worth PLN 914 million have been awarded throughout the country. Polish families have already made 318 thousand. tourist voucher payments in the amount of PLN 232 million.\r\n\r\nCooperation beyond divisions\r\n\r\nPrime minister Mateusz Morawiecki met again with representatives of the opposition and the presidents of major cities. The discussions focused on health services and the response to the Coronavirus outbreak. This is not the first meeting of this kind between members of the government and the opposition. Representatives of the parliamentary clubs have already been consulted on the difficult situation in Belarus. We are open to dialogue. The Coronavirus outbreak is a test of social solidarity for all, as well as the ability to work beyond divisions', 'Expanding strategy to fight coronavirus', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'expanding-strategy-to-fight-coronavirus', '', '', '2020-11-04 16:22:54', '2020-11-04 13:22:54', '', 0, 'https://blessedfirm.com/?p=867', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(869, 1, '2020-11-04 16:22:54', '2020-11-04 13:22:54', 'The health and safety of citizens is of the utmost importance to us. We are taking further steps to make the fight against coronavirus more effective. We\'re accelerating testing of patients with suspected covid-19. For this purpose, we will use antigen tests, the result of which is known after a few minutes. The health status of people who do not have symptoms or are mild will be monitored with a pulse oximeter-all to relieve the burden on hospitals and medical facilities. We appreciate the work of the medical services-we grant additional benefits to doctors, nurses, laboratory diagnosticians and rescuers and increase their maximum amount.\r\n\r\nExpanded coronavirus strategy\r\nExpanding coronavirus strategy-what will change?\r\nThe pulse oximeter will monitor your health at home\r\n\r\nA pulse oximeter is a small electronic device. It is used for non-invasive measurement of blood saturation. It will soon assist the medical services in monitoring the health status of COVID-19 patients who are experiencing the disease in a mild manner and have been qualified for home medical care. The data transmitted by the device will be analyzed by a special monitoring center. This will be a new unit, which will be appointed by the Ministry of health.\r\n\r\nThe result even in a few minutes thanks to antigen tests\r\n\r\nUntil now, the main test used to confirm coronavirus infection has been PCR. In order for testing to go faster, we will also use antigen tests more often than before. This test can detect the presence of viral protein in patients with high numbers of viral particles in the airway epithelium. The test result is already known from 10 to 30 min.\r\n\r\nLarger insulator base\r\n\r\nAn isolation ward is a place where people infected with coronavirus recover. Patients who cannot be isolated in their own home-for example, because they live with people from the high-risk group-are referred to insulators. There are also patients who were in the hospital, but their condition is good enough that they can continue treatment in the isolation ward.\r\n\r\nSo far, we\'ve had 6,500 available in the isolation wards. beds. We\'ll increase the number to 10,000. in 55 facilities throughout Poland.\r\n\r\nAdditional benefits for medical services\r\n\r\nWe appreciate and are grateful to the medical services for their daily work. We pay an additional benefit for medical personnel who are involved in the fight against covid-19. More than 30,000 so far. people from the medical staff were in quarantine. After this decision, the medical staff will not be quarantined, thanks to the daily antigen tests \" - said the head of the kprm Micha≈Ç Dworczyk.\r\n\r\nHospital at PGE National ‚Äì the first stage of work is coming to an end\r\n\r\nThe first phase of the construction of the hospital at PGE national is coming to an end. All electrical and oxygen work has been completed. Finishing and cleaning works are currently underway. As part of the hospital are already ready m.in:\r\n\r\npatient\'s emergency room,\r\nsick room equipped with 285 beds of which 16 are intended for intensive care,\r\nIntensive Surveillance Unit,\r\ntreatment room,\r\nimaging laboratories equipped with 4 mobile X-ray machines and tomograph,\r\nhospital pharmacy department,\r\nmedicine room.\r\nThe temporary hospital at the PGE national stadium will be equipped with 160 cardiomonitors, 45 respirators, 4 mobile X-rays, 3 oxygen generators, 2 ultrasounds. In addition, in 45 km of electrical wires and 5 km of copper tubes to oxygen.\r\n\r\nAt this stage, the hospital has 300 beds available. We are starting work on the second stage-after its completion, the number of beds will increase from 300 to 500. On November 16, another temporary hospital will start operating in Warsaw-the EXPO XXI center in Warsaw.\r\n\r\nTemporary hospital in every voivodship\r\n\r\nThe temporary hospital, which is being built at the PGE national stadium, will not be the only such facility in the country. At least one hospital for COVID-19 patients will be established in each province. Most of them will be put into operation between 15 and 30 November. Thanks to these actions, the base of hospital beds for patients infected with coronavirus will increase by more than 5 thousand. places.\r\n\r\nMost temporary hospitals will be built in convention and exhibition centers and sports halls. These will not be facilities that are currently used by the health service. The cost of adaptation of objects (not including equipment) will be about 130 million rubles.\r\n\r\nFind out where to build a hospital in your province:\r\n\r\nvoivodship dolno≈õlƒÖskie: Terminal Hotel Centrum Konferencyjne, at UL. Rakietowa 33 in Wroc≈Çaw,\r\nvoivodship kujawsko-pomorskie: 22. Military Hospital SP ZOZ at UL. Wojska Polskiego 5 in Ciechocin,\r\nvoivodship lubelskie: Targi Lublin S. A., at UL. Dworcowa 11 in Lublin\r\nlubuskie Voivodeship: Centre for Maternal and Child Health, at Zyty 26 in Zielona G√≥ra,\r\n≈Ç√≥d≈∫ Voivodeship: EXPO-≈Å√ìD≈π Sp√≥≈Çka z o. o., at UL. Politechniki 4 in ≈Ç√≥d≈∫,\r\nvoivodship ma≈Çopolskie: Trauma Centre For Emergency Medicine and catastrophes at UL. Miko≈Çaja Kopernika 50 and EXPO Krak√≥w at UL. Galicyjska 9 in Krak√≥w,\r\nmazowieckie Voivodeship: Warsaw Expo XXI Centre, at Ignacy PrƒÖdzy≈Ñski 12/14 and PGE National Stadium, Prince J√≥zef Poniatowski Avenue 1 in Warsaw\r\nOpole Voivodeship: exhibition and Congress Centre, 158 Wroc≈Çawska Street, Opole,\r\nvoivodship podkarpackie: SP ZOZ MSWiA, at ul. ul. Krakowska 16 in Rzesz√≥w,\r\npodlaskie Voivodeship: Sports Hall of the Medical University, 1 Micha≈Ç Wo≈Çodyjowski Street and building E1 of the University Clinical Hospital, 14 ≈ªurawiej Street in Bia≈Çystok,\r\nPomeranian Voivodeship: Sanatorium MSWiA, 63-65 Bitwy pod P≈Çowcami Street in Sopot,\r\nSilesian Voivodeship: International Congress Centre, s≈Çawika and Antalla square 1 in Katowice,\r\nvoivodship ≈õwiƒôtokrzyskie: Targi Kielce SA, at UL. Zak≈Çadowa 1 in Kielce,\r\nvoivodship warmi≈Ñsko-mazurskie: Health Care Unit, at UL. Mickiewicza 25 in Nidzica and Health Care Unit, at UL. Maria Sk≈Çodowska-Curie 12 in Szczytno,\r\nvoivodship wielkopolskie: Pozna≈Ñ International Fair, at 14 G≈Çogowska Street in Pozna≈Ñ,\r\nvoivodship zachodniopomorskie: Netto arena, ul.w≈Çadys≈Çawa szafera 3/5/7 and independent public Clinical Hospital No. 2, al. Powsta≈Ñc√≥w wielkopolskich 72 in Szczecin.\r\nWe care about our seniors\r\n\r\nThe elderly are the most vulnerable group to coronavirus infection. That is why we are introducing solutions that will help us protect our parents or grandparents.\r\n\r\nSenior stay at home and use the special hotline - 22 505 11 11\r\n\r\nIn recent days, we have launched a Solidarity Corps to support seniors. One of the pillars of this project is a dedicated helpline for people over 70. one year old. So far, nearly 8 thousand have used it. persons. The aim of the helpline is to support seniors in everyday activities that require leaving home-especially shopping.\r\n\r\nAll persons who would like to participate in the #Supportsenior campaign can do so via the website www.wspierajseniora.pl.to date, the desire to help declared nearly 6 thousand. volunteers from all over the country!\r\n\r\nAdditional measures for social welfare homes\r\n\r\nIn October, we mobilized PLN 38 million from the state budget for the preparation and protection of DPS against an increase in coronavirus infections in the autumn period. As much as PLN 328 million from the European Social Fund and the state budget goes to social assistance homes for current needs related to the coronavirus epidemic. For the daily sacrifice and commitment to the duties performed, DPS employees can also count on salary supplements.\r\n\r\nAnti-crisis shield protects Polish entrepreneurs from crisis\r\n\r\nWe protect businesses and millions of jobs from the coronavirus. Our goal is to provide employees with stable employment, and companies-opportunities for development. The effectiveness of our actions is confirmed by the data. Polish companies have already received more than PLN 148 billion under the anti-crisis and financial shield.\r\n\r\nWe are also supporting the tourism industry during this difficult period. To date, more than 1 million tourist vouchers worth PLN 914 million have been awarded throughout the country. Polish families have already made 318 thousand. tourist voucher payments in the amount of PLN 232 million.\r\n\r\nCooperation beyond divisions\r\n\r\nPrime minister Mateusz Morawiecki met again with representatives of the opposition and the presidents of major cities. The discussions focused on health services and the response to the Coronavirus outbreak. This is not the first meeting of this kind between members of the government and the opposition. Representatives of the parliamentary clubs have already been consulted on the difficult situation in Belarus. We are open to dialogue. The Coronavirus outbreak is a test of social solidarity for all, as well as the ability to work beyond divisions', 'Expanding strategy to fight coronavirus', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '867-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-11-04 16:22:54', '2020-11-04 13:22:54', '', 867, 'https://blessedfirm.com/blog/2020/11/04/867-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
